            "id": "a82bca516a3c41c2ba084",
            "questionText": "A family is decorating their house for the holidays with a new string of LED lights. These lights are designed with individual LED lamps connected in parallel. If there are $!$20$!$ identical LED lamps in the string, each with a resistance of $!$50 \\Omega$!$, and the entire string is powered by an adapter providing a potential difference of $!$10 \\text{V}$!$, calculate the total current drawn from the adapter when all lights are on.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "8ca4eb98cebe4819ad5e3",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by understanding the connection type of the LED lamps. In a parallel circuit, a particular electrical property is the same across each device. Please select the correct concept that represents this property.",
